[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Testing zlib decompression**\n\nI need to check the zlib decompression using actual compressed data, considering whether to set nowrap to true or false in java.util.zip.Deflater. The Hadoop direct decompressor likely requires a direct buffer, so I'll test that. I’m wondering if native images should support dynamic zlib decompression. It seems like I should ensure no deprecated APIs are involved and verify the use of DirectDecompressor. \n\nI might also want to test specific configurations, but I'll need to avoid duplicating existing tests while ensuring direct decompression functionality is covered properly.\n\n**Testing direct decompressor behavior**\n\nI’m considering whether the wrapper reset should handle two payloads with the same decompressor. This is a functional feature where the direct decompressor needs to manage both wrapped and no-header zlib streams effectively, allowing reuse. I need to understand if the output buffer will flip and how the Hadoop ZlibDirectDecompressor behaves—likely consuming input, writing output, and updating positions without flipping.\n\nI'll write a helper for testing this behavior and compile with IOException considerations. After decompressing, I’ll check if the output’s position corresponds to its length, ensuring I manage the use of direct ByteBuffer correctly. I should also verify the relationship between Deflater settings for both header types.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0832257ffadd7b600169fe5d11db208190a5d0b53b2d82fbef\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_l0bWzfv0fPyVlfKzcBhhkPWYiX8fMGuYkKai8DwKbO_4USCpP4XEVf4h2NN-PM4Bbe6mKuEcXNby4URwCeNzgVoBCdweKwUmcXDzk0AOAP-kdBRZbS3YPjLrvk_SXmtBAPoncysGWMAfSaQ6z0xqAj5b_bUMHQbDs5US7OJu1XNZwlSfjvcEyyTuudkZMp8s6c_o3gHQEmz7XUxkEdwiX6KqRhITUIOau3G2q30cl7vKpoS7wGrq_NffETKPv-peJZy2SVSnI2qo3WyT86leWNFTCM4PvdKZNFEL-PQt12SGwAROG6uLcGuKdD7E5aSUGM5fet8OZr2D